HEADWORD: Countershaft
<hw>Coun"ter*shaft`</hw> <pr>(koun"t?r-sh?ft`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Mach.)</fld> <def>An intermediate shaft; esp., one which receives
motion from a line shaft in a factory and transmits it to a
machine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

